_comment: Example web search results for 'AI news this week'. This is the expected format of the 'results' array returned by the web_search tool.

results.title: Google I/O 2024: AI takes center stage
results.snippet: Google's annual developer conference showcased the latest advancements in AI, including Gemini 1.5 Pro, Imagen 3, and Project Astra. Key announcements focused on improving AI's reasoning, multimodal capabilities, and real-time interaction.

results.title: OpenAI unveils new GPT-4o model
results.snippet: OpenAI released GPT-4o, a new flagship model that enhances multimodal capabilities, including processing text, audio, and vision inputs in real-time. The model is significantly faster and cheaper than GPT-4.

results.title: AI ethics concerns grow as models become more powerful
results.snippet: Experts warn about the potential risks of increasingly powerful AI models, including bias, misinformation, and job displacement. Discussions around AI regulation and ethical guidelines are intensifying.

results.title: Microsoft Build 2024: AI-powered developer tools
results.snippet: Microsoft highlighted new AI-powered developer tools at its annual Build conference, including enhanced Copilot features, AI-assisted coding, and cloud services optimized for AI workloads. They focused on empowering developers with AI.

results.title: AI investment surges to record levels in Q2 2024
results.snippet: Venture capital investment in AI startups reached a new high in the second quarter of 2024, driven by advancements in generative AI and machine learning. The report analyzes the latest funding trends and deals in the AI space.
